  "hypothesis": "You ought to help the stranger in medical distress.",
  "label": "Conflict within one principle",
  "explanation": "Crying typically indicates emotional distress. Given that you should promote others’ wellbeing, emotional distress is a reason to comfort the first stranger. Given that you should promote others’ wellbeing, medical danger is a reason to help the second stranger. Because reasons based on urgent physical danger are stronger, the reason to help the stranger in medical distress takes priority."
