    "hypothesis": "You ought to avoid exposing the two people.",
    "label": "Conflict within one principle",
    "explanation": "Exposure to a dangerous chemical typically indicates harm. Given that you shall do no harm, the harm to one person is a reason not to expose the one, and the harm to two people is a reason not to expose the two. Because preventing greater harm provides the stronger reason, the reason to avoid exposing the two people is stronger."
