    "explanation": "A death indicates serious harm. Given that you shall do no harm, preventing one death is a reason to avoid pushing the button, and preventing two deaths is a reason to push it. Because preventing greater harm provides the stronger reason, the reason to prevent two deaths takes priority and you ought to push the button."
