    "label": "Conflict within one principle",
    "explanation": "A death indicates serious harm. Given that you shall do no harm, preventing one death is a reason to avoid pushing the button and preventing two deaths is a reason to push it. But actively causing harm typically provides a stronger reason against action. Because avoiding actively causing harm takes priority, the reason not to push the button is stronger."
